{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779169323920,"sessionID":"ses_1c140733cfferaKPqrrV4oeTVj","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_00_47KpWeuC4Kbc3Q2Jds4H7287","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore codebase structure","prompt":"Explore the codebase structure thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. What exists under backend/src/core/base/ - read ALL files there, especially base.entity.ts\n2. What exists under backend/src/common/enums/ or backend/src/shared/enums/ \n3. What exists under backend/src/modules/ - any existing modules/entities\n4. What exists under backend/src/database/migrations/\n5. The backend/src/ directory structure (package.json, tsconfig, app.module.ts etc.)\n6. Read the full PROJECT_DATABASE.md at /Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_DATABASE.md\n\nReturn:\n- The FULL content of base.entity.ts\n- List of existing files under core/base/\n- List of existing enums\n- List of existing entities\n- List of existing migrations\n- The FULL content of PROJECT_DATABASE.md\n- The backend package.json\n- The backend tsconfig.json","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_1c1401497ffeeehFyMbf8Ur2U1 (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere is the complete exploration report.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Complete Codebase Structure Overview\n\nThe backend is at a very early stage -- it has the core scaffolding in place but no modules, entities, enums, or migrations have been created yet. Here is the full directory tree:\n\n```\nbackend/\n├── node_modules/\n├── package-lock.json\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n└── src/\n    ├── app.module.ts\n    ├── main.ts\n    └── core/\n        └── base/\n            ├── base.controller.ts\n            ├── base.entity.ts\n            ├── base.repository.ts\n            ├── base.service.ts\n            └── index.ts\n```\n\n**Missing / Empty directories:**\n- `backend/src/modules/` -- **does not exist** (no feature modules created)\n- `backend/src/common/enums/` -- **does not exist**\n- `backend/src/shared/enums/` -- **does not exist**\n- `backend/src/database/migrations/` -- **does not exist**\n- `backend/src/infrastructure/` -- **does not exist**\n\n---\n\n## 2. Full Content of `base.entity.ts`\n\n**File:** `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/base.entity.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport {\n    PrimaryGeneratedColumn,\n    CreateDateColumn,\n    UpdateDateColumn,\n    DeleteDateColumn,\n} from 'typeorm';\n\nexport abstract class BaseEntity {\n    @PrimaryGeneratedColumn('uuid')\n    id: string;\n\n    @CreateDateColumn({ name: 'created_at', type: 'timestamp' })\n    createdAt: Date;\n\n    @UpdateDateColumn({ name: 'updated_at', type: 'timestamp' })\n    updatedAt: Date;\n\n    @DeleteDateColumn({ name: 'deleted_at', type: 'timestamp', nullable: true })\n    deletedAt: Date | null;\n}\n```\n\nKey details:\n- **`id`**: UUID primary key, auto-generated.\n- **`createdAt`**: auto-managed `timestamp`, mapped to column `created_at`.\n- **`updatedAt`**: auto-managed `timestamp`, mapped to column `updated_at`.\n- **`deletedAt`**: soft-delete column (`nullable: true`), mapped to `deleted_at`. This enables TypeORM soft-delete behavior on entities that extend this class.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Files Under `core/base/`\n\n| File | Path | Purpose |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `base.entity.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/base.entity.ts` | Abstract entity with `id`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `deletedAt` |\n| `base.repository.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/base.repository.ts` | Generic CRUD repository wrapping TypeORM's `Repository` -- `findAll`, `findById`, `findOne`, `create`, `update`, `softDelete`, `delete`, `count` |\n| `base.service.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/base.service.ts` | Generic service with `findByIdOrFail` (throws `NotFoundException`), `findAll`, `create`, `update`, `remove` (soft-delete), `delete` (hard-delete) |\n| `base.controller.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/base.controller.ts` | Generic REST controller with `POST /`, `GET /`, `GET /:id`, `PATCH /:id`, `DELETE /:id` -- Swagger-decorated, `ParseUUIDPipe` on ID params, pagination via `page`/`limit` query params |\n| `index.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/index.ts` | Barrel export: `BaseEntity`, `BaseRepository`, `BaseService`, `BaseController` |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Enums\n\n**No enum files exist anywhere in the codebase** (neither under `common/enums/` nor `shared/enums/`).\n\nThe `PROJECT_DATABASE.md` specifies four enums that need to be created:\n\n| Enum | Values |\n|------|--------|\n| `RoleEnum` | `renter`, `admin` |\n| `UserStatusEnum` | `active`, `suspended` |\n| `PropertyTypeEnum` | `apartment`, `house`, `condo`, `townhouse`, `studio` |\n| `InquiryStatusEnum` | `new`, `read`, `responded` |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing Entities\n\n**No entity files exist.** The `modules/` directory is entirely empty (it does not even exist yet).\n\nThe `PROJECT_DATABASE.md` specifies these entities need to be created:\n\n| Entity | Table | Extends BaseEntity | Soft Delete |\n|--------|-------|--------------------|-------------|\n| `User` | `users` | Yes | Yes |\n| `RefreshToken` | `refresh_tokens` | No (standalone) | No (`revoked_at` + `expires_at`) |\n| `PasswordResetToken` | `password_reset_tokens` | No (standalone) | No (`expires_at` + `used_at`) |\n| `Property` | `properties` | Yes | Yes |\n| `PropertyPhoto` | `property_photos` | Yes | No |\n| `Amenity` | `amenities` | Yes | Yes |\n| `PropertyAmenity` | `property_amenities` | Junction only | No |\n| `Favorite` | `favorites` | Yes | No |\n| `Inquiry` | `inquiries` | Yes | No |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Existing Migrations\n\n**No migrations exist.** The `database/` directory is empty.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Backend `package.json`\n\n**File:** `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/package.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"backend\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\",\n    \"build\": \"tsc\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@nestjs/common\": \"^10.3.0\",\n    \"@nestjs/core\": \"^10.3.0\",\n    \"@nestjs/typeorm\": \"^10.0.2\",\n    \"class-transformer\": \"^0.5.1\",\n    \"class-validator\": \"^0.14.1\",\n    \"reflect-metadata\": \"^0.2.2\",\n    \"rxjs\": \"^7.8.1\",\n    \"typeorm\": \"^0.3.20\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@types/node\": \"^20.12.7\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.5\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- Only two scripts: `typecheck` and `build`. Missing: `start`, `dev`, `test`, `migration:generate`, `migration:run`.\n- Dependencies include NestJS core, TypeORM, class-validator/class-transformer. Missing: `@nestjs/swagger`, `@nestjs/config`, `@nestjs/jwt`, `passport`, `bcrypt`, `pg` (PostgreSQL driver), `cookie-parser`.\n- No `@nestjs/cli` in dependencies or devDependencies.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Backend `tsconfig.json`\n\n**File:** `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/tsconfig.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"module\": \"commonjs\",\n    \"target\": \"es2021\",\n    \"lib\": [\"es2021\"],\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"node\",\n    \"experimentalDecorators\": true,\n    \"emitDecoratorMetadata\": true,\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"strictPropertyInitialization\": false,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n    \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true,\n    \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\n    \"noEmit\": true,\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"baseUrl\": \"./\"\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*.ts\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"test\"]\n}\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- `strict: true` with `strictPropertyInitialization: false` (needed for TypeORM decorator patterns).\n- `experimentalDecorators: true` and `emitDecoratorMetadata: true` -- required for NestJS and TypeORM.\n- `module: \"commonjs\"`, `target: \"es2021\"` -- standard NestJS configuration.\n- No path aliases defined (no `paths` mapping).\n- `noEmit: true` means `tsc` is used only for type-checking; no compiled output is generated. This implies a separate build tool (like `@nestjs/cli`'s webpack bundler or `ts-node`) would be needed for actual runtime.\n\n---\n\n## 9. `app.module.ts` and `main.ts`\n\n**`app.module.ts`** -- Bare minimum:\n```typescript\nimport { Module } from '@nestjs/common';\n\n@Module({\n  imports: [],\n  controllers: [],\n  providers: [],\n})\nexport class AppModule {}\n```\n\n**`main.ts`** -- Basic NestJS bootstrap:\n```typescript\nimport { NestFactory } from '@nestjs/core';\nimport { AppModule } from './app.module';\n\nasync function bootstrap(): Promise<void> {\n  const app = await NestFactory.create(AppModule);\n  app.setGlobalPrefix('api');\n  await app.listen(3000);\n}\n\nvoid bootstrap();\n```\n\nThe `AppModule` has no TypeORM connection, no validation pipe, no cookie parser, no CORS config -- all of which will need to be added.\n\n---\n\n## 10. `PROJECT_DATABASE.md` (already shown in full above)\n\nFor reference, the file is at:\n**`/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_DATABASE.md`** (394 lines)\n\nIt fully specifies:\n- 9 entities with complete column definitions, constraints, indexes, and relationships\n- 4 enums\n- Foreign key summary table\n- Relationship diagram\n- Naming conventions (snake_case tables/columns, PascalCase+Enum for TypeScript enums)\n- Soft-delete rules per entity\n- Data type conventions\n\n---\n\n## Summary: Current State vs. What's Needed\n\n| Artifact | Status | Count Needed per Spec |\n|----------|--------|-----------------------|\n| Base layer (`core/base/`) | **Complete** (5 files) | N/A -- already done |\n| Enums | **Missing** | 4 enum files |\n| Entity files | **Missing** | 9 entity files |\n| Modules (feature) | **Missing** | ~6-7 modules (users, auth, properties, amenities, favorites, inquiries) |\n| Migrations | **Missing** | At least 1 initial migration |\n| `AppModule` wiring | **Bare skeleton** | Needs TypeORM, ConfigModule, feature modules imported |\n| `main.ts` config | **Minimal** | Needs ValidationPipe, cookie-parser, CORS, swagger setup |\n| Package dependencies | **Partial** | Missing: pg, bcrypt, @nestjs/jwt, @nestjs/config, @nestjs/swagger, passport, cookie-parser, @nestjs/cli |\n</task_result>","metadata":{"parentSessionId":"ses_1c140733cfferaKPqrrV4oeTVj","sessionId":"ses_1c1401497ffeeehFyMbf8Ur2U1","model":{"modelID":"deepseek-v4-pro","providerID":"opencode-go"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore codebase structure","time":{"start":1779169225581,"end":1779169323918}},"id":"prt_e3ebfca13001NkLufU1Zq7rXjm","sessionID":"ses_1c140733cfferaKPqrrV4oeTVj","messageID":"msg_e3ebfbaf0001MAw0sQC3wH8t5U"}}
